The area has a quite{good } communications system. There are railway stations in{South Elmsall} and {Moorthorpe. South Elmsall} has connections with {main line} stations at{Doncaster and Leeds, Moorthorpe}is on the{Rotherham to York}line. The principle goods transported is{coal} the wagons are known as the {"Merry-go-round",}operate{24 hrs}per day to the{power stations.}
The roads through{South Elmsall/South {Kirkby}make easy access to the{A1 {(North/South)}and the{M62 (East/West).
The{bus services}are quite efficient with a small bus station and regular services to {Doncaster, Wakefield, {Pontefract}and {Barnsley.}
